File: John Steenhuisen, the leader Democratic Alliance (DA)RODGER BOSCH / AFP JOHANNESBURG - South Africans need to see that coalition governments can be stable and take the country forward, according to DA leader, John Steenhuisen. He says it was challenging to get parties to reach agreements after the elections. READ: LIVESTREAM | Multi-party coalition formation in Gauteng sign new agreements New multi-party coalition agreements were signed in Johannesburg, Tshwane, and Ekhuruleni on Tuesday. It's hoped they will help fast-track service delivery.